registeredWorkshops.name: Painting with Watercolour
registeredWorkshops.description: This workshop will focus on basic watercolour techniques. Students will get to paint something from nature, and through the exercise identify some interesting nuances about perception and colour using watercolour. After you are equipped with these new skills and knowledge, you’ll be free to create your own unique starry galaxy landscapes!

registeredWorkshops.name: Paint Scrapes
registeredWorkshops.description: Paint Scrapes is an easy activity where everyone can get involved. It is a process of color mixing, where participants can add a small amount of paint on a paper or canvas, and use a piece of pre-cut cardboard to drag it across the paper to push the paint in any direction they like. They can repeat the process and try scraping it over the previous colors to blend the paint.
